\emph on
Can you distinguish an organised structure across yourself and your colleagues?
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
Evidence available in REF3 points out to a non-trivial structure for professiona
ls within Company X.
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" rightline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
The organization was clearly delinated into a matrix structure including
 project organizations, business divisions and supporting functions.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
</row>
<row>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
\emph on
Do you and the colleagues you work with work in the same single site?
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
In page 68 of REF 2, authors stress that many people worked off-site on
 the same product.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" rightline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
No, the organisation is highly dispersed over dozens of sites.
 At least five major sites in three timezones.
 Many sites comprise only one or two people.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
</row>
<row>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
\emph on
Do you work in a highly-distributed setting with few teams or colleagues
 per location?
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
In page 69 of REF 2 and following, data states that a technology for localizatio
n and involvement of people from off-site was used.
 However, some conflicting statements on REF 1 suggest that division of
 work was organised by assigning products and product lines to single sites.
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" rightline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
The organization was dispersed over dozens of sites, with at least five
 major sites in three timezones.
 Many sites had one or two people only.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
</row>
<row>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
\emph on
Do you and your fellow colleagues interact informally only?
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
Selection and governance protocols are still in action to request additional
 people to work on certain tasks (page 84 of REF 2 + AGILE SLIDES).
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" rightline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
There were lots of organization-wide intranet and internet tools that (semi-)for
malized the interaction around certain topics like product management and
 defect tracking 
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
</row>
<row>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
\emph on
Do you work on time-bound projects?
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
In page 2 of AGILE SLIDES the strategic portfolio duration (i.e.
 the set of projects planned) is fixed to increments of 2-5 years.
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" rightline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
Teams were responsible for a technology domain, such as “multimedia” or
 “connectivity” over a long period of time.
 Components and technologies changed but the team remained.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
</row>
<row>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
\emph on
Do you and your colleagues disseminate or increase the visibility of your
 work? 
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
In page 59 states that all items and backlogs and all operations are explicitly
 planned to be visible and transparent.
 Therefore visibility is actively pursued NOT by members but by hand of
 their organizational sponsor.
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" rightline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
Unfortunately, the teams formed their own information silos regarding project
 and product metadata.
 Teams were reactive rather than proactive in dissipating information.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
</row>
<row>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
\emph on
Do you and your colleagues actively try to team-build? 
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
In page 30 and 65, REF 1 authors note that anywhere in the organizational
 structure, the intervention of senior management is needed to provide attention
 for quality, value and encouragement/bonding.
 These are consistent with increasing the cohesion of the Scrum team.
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" rightline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
The organization didn’t explicitly promote cohesion, this involves all team-buil
ding exercises.
 None of such exercises were proposed nor promoted.
 However, the Scrum working model proposes reasoning and reflection sessions
 that increase cohesion.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
</row>
<row>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
\emph on
Do you need to explicitly demonstrate ROI to your organization? 
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
In page 64 and subsequent, REF 2 states that demos were acting as checkpoints
 for customers to evaluate ROI.
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
<cell alignment="left" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" rightline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\size footnotesize
Software development projects only indirectly contributed to the product.
 As a new R&D project, ROI requirements were postponed.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
</row>
